## 3. TypeScript Rules

```typescript
// ✅ Always type function parameters and return values
async function getEvent(id: string): Promise<Event | null> { ... }

// ✅ Use `type` not `interface` (ESLint enforces this)
type EventRole = 'owner' | 'co_host' | 'coordinator' | 'dj' | 'guest' | 'vip_guest' | 'vendor';

// ✅ Infer Drizzle types from the schema
import type { InferSelectModel } from 'drizzle-orm';
import { eventSchema } from '@/models/Schema';
type Event = InferSelectModel<typeof eventSchema>;

// ❌ Never do this
const data: any = await fetch(...);
const event = data as Event;
```

- Use `type` everywhere — the ESLint config enforces `ts/consistent-type-definitions: ['error', 'type']`
- Import types with `import type { ... }` to avoid runtime imports
- All Zod schemas live in `packages/validators` — never define validation schemas inline in components

---

## 4. Database (Drizzle) Rules

```typescript
// ✅ Schema goes in apps/web/src/models/Schema.ts
// ✅ Always import db from @/libs/DB
import { db } from '@/libs/DB';
import { eventSchema } from '@/models/Schema';
import { eq, and, desc } from 'drizzle-orm';

// ✅ Type-safe queries
const event = await db.query.eventSchema.findFirst({
  where: eq(eventSchema.id, eventId),
});

// ✅ After any schema change:
// npm run db:generate --filter=@saas/web
// npm run db:migrate --filter=@saas/web

// ❌ Never
db.execute(sql`SELECT * FROM events WHERE id = ${eventId}`);
```

- The `organization`, `member`, and `invitation` tables will be added by running `npx @better-auth/cli generate` after the `organization()` plugin is added to `auth.ts`
- Better Auth tables (`userTable`, `sessionTable`, etc.) live in `AuthSchema.ts` — never modify these manually
- Bashly business tables (events, rsvps, songs, invites, etc.) live in `Schema.ts`
- Always run `db:generate` + `db:migrate` after schema changes — never edit migration files manually

---

## 5. Authentication Rules

```typescript
// ✅ Server-side session check
import { auth } from '@/libs/auth';
import { headers } from 'next/headers';

const session = await auth.api.getSession({ headers: await headers() });
if (!session) redirect('/sign-in');

// ✅ Client-side session
import { useSession } from '@/libs/auth-client';
const { data: session } = useSession();

// ❌ Never access Better Auth internals directly
// ❌ Never write custom JWT logic
// ❌ Never store session data in localStorage
```

- Guest-facing RSVP and song request endpoints are unauthenticated — check event slug + fingerprint, not session
- Role checks for dashboard actions: verify `event_roles` table entry for the current user + event ID
- Never trust client-supplied role claims — always verify server-side against the database

---

## 6. API Route Rules

```typescript
// ✅ Standard pattern for authenticated API routes
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';
import { auth } from '@/libs/auth';
import { headers } from 'next/headers';

export async function GET(req: NextRequest) {
  const session = await auth.api.getSession({ headers: await headers() });
  if (!session) return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });

  // ... handler logic
}

// ✅ Standard pattern for unauthenticated guest endpoints (RSVP, song request)
export async function POST(req: NextRequest, { params }: { params: { slug: string } }) {
  const body = await req.json();
  const parsed = rsvpSchema.safeParse(body);
  if (!parsed.success) return NextResponse.json({ error: parsed.error }, { status: 400 });
  // ... no session check needed
}
```

- All API routes in `apps/web/src/app/[locale]/api/` or `apps/web/src/app/api/` (locale-agnostic preferred for API)
- Always validate request bodies with Zod before touching the database
- Return consistent error shapes: `{ error: string, code?: string }`
- Rate-limit the iTunes search proxy and guest RSVP endpoints

