## 7. UI & Styling Rules

### Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- Always use Tailwind utility classes — never write custom CSS
- Use shadcn/ui components as the base; extend with Bashly design tokens from `tailwind.config.ts`
- Import shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/`
- `cn()` utility (from `@/utils/Helpers`) for conditional class merging — never string concatenation

### Bashly Design Tokens (from brand guidelines)
```
Fonts:
  - Headings: Bricolage Grotesque, weight 800
  - Body: Nunito, weight 400/600/700
  - Labels/numbers/dates/counts: JetBrains Mono, weight 600

Light mode key colors:
  - bg: rgb(248 251 254)
  - surface: #ffffff
  - text: rgb(9 21 27)
  - accent (light): rgb(48 153 0)  ← fern-700, text/icons only
  - CTA bg: rgb(81 255 0)          ← fern-500, buttons ONLY
  - CTA text: cerulean-950

Dark mode key colors:
  - bg: rgb(9 21 27)
  - surface: rgb(12 24 33)
  - text: rgb(236 244 249)
  - accent (dark): rgb(116 255 51) ← fern-400

Rules:
  - fern-500 (bright green) is ONLY used as CTA button backgrounds
  - Never use fern-500 as text color on light backgrounds
  - All text must meet WCAG AA: 4.5:1 for body, 3:1 for large text
  - All touch targets: minimum 44×44px
  - Buttons: pill-shaped (border-radius: 100px), min-height 44px, Nunito 700
  - All numbers, dates, counts, metadata: JetBrains Mono
  - Section labels: JetBrains Mono 0.6875rem, 600 weight, uppercase, 0.18em tracking, accent color
```

### Accessibility (non-negotiable)
- Every interactive element needs `aria-label` or visible label
- Focus rings: `outline: 3px solid var(--focus-ring); outline-offset: 3px` — never `outline: none`
- All modals: `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, `aria-labelledby`, focus trap on open, restore focus on close
- Images: always `alt` text; decorative images use `alt=""`
- Motion: wrap animations in `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)`
- Screen reader text for icon-only buttons: use `.sr-only` class
- Live regions: toasts/notifications use `role="status"` or `aria-live="polite"`

