## 8. i18n Rules

- All user-facing strings must go through `next-intl` — never hardcode English strings in JSX
- String keys live in `apps/web/src/locales/en.json` and `es.json`
- Use `useTranslations('ComponentName')` in client components
- Use `getTranslations('ComponentName')` in server components and API routes
- Never use `t('key')` from a different namespace without declaring the namespace

```typescript
// ✅ Server component
const t = await getTranslations('EventDetail');
// ✅ Client component
const t = useTranslations('EventDetail');
// ❌ Never
<p>Welcome to your dashboard</p>
```

---

## 9. Commit Rules

All commits must follow Conventional Commits format. Use `npm run commit` (Commitizen) — never write commit messages manually.

Format: `type(scope): description`

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `style`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`
Scopes: `web`, `mobile`, `auth`, `db`, `events`, `music`, `rsvp`, `registry`, `billing`, `api`

Examples:
- `feat(events): add event creation multi-step form`
- `fix(auth): add organization plugin to auth.ts`
- `refactor(db): replace todoSchema with Bashly event tables`

---

## 10. What NOT to Generate

- ❌ No `interface` — use `type`
- ❌ No `any` — ever
- ❌ No Pages Router files (`pages/` directory)
- ❌ No raw SQL strings
- ❌ No Clerk imports or references
- ❌ No Todo-related code (being removed)
- ❌ No hardcoded English strings in JSX
- ❌ No `outline: none` on focusable elements
- ❌ No fern-500 as text color on light backgrounds
- ❌ No `StyleSheet.create` in mobile code — use NativeWind
- ❌ No `@radix-ui/*` imports in `apps/mobile/`
- ❌ No `localStorage` for auth tokens (use `expo-secure-store` on mobile, Better Auth cookies on web)
- ❌ No Edge runtime on auth/stripe/R2 routes
